tafsir[19]{c,v,t}:
  81,1,"When the mass of the sun is gathered and its light vanishes."
  81,2,"When the stars fall one after the other and their light is taken away."
  81,3,"When the mountains are moved from their places."
  81,5,"When wild animals are gathered with human beings on one plain."
  81,6,"When the seas are lit until they become a fire."
  81,7,"When souls are joined with their likeness. A sinner will be joined with a sinner and a pious person will be joined with a pious person."
  81,8,"When the girl buried alive is asked by Allah."
  81,9,"For what crime were you killed by the person who killed you?"
  81,11,"When the sky is stripped like how the skin is stripped away from a sheep."
  81,12,"When the Fire is lit."
  81,13,"When Paradise is brought near to those who are Mindful."
  81,15,"Allah took an oath by the stars that are hidden until they emerge at night."
  81,18,"He took an oath by the morning when its light emerges."
  81,21,"He is obeyed by the inhabitants of the heavens and trusted in the revelation that he conveys."
  81,23,"Your companion had seen Gabriel in the form that he was created in the clear horizon of the sky."
  81,25,"This Qur’ān is not the speech of a satan distanced from Allah’s mercy."
  81,26,"So which path will you tread to deny that it is from Allah after all these evidence?!"
  81,27,"The Qur’ān is only a reminder and counsel to the jinn and mankind."
  81,28,"For those of you who wish to be steadfast on the path of truth."